HEADWORD: Tidewaiter
<hw>Tide"wait`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A customhouse
officer who watches the landing of goods from merchant vessels, in order
to secure payment of duties.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

